    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Suspended structures used to protect the altar in a church, or to designate the altar as the place of greatest importance in the space. When an altar canopy is made of fabric, it consists of a roof with hangings and sometimes curtains.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
